Diagnosis.
Male surstyli asymmetrical, with 3 (right side) or 4 (left side) long ventral and 3 short dorsal spines on apical margin (
Fig. 27A
). Female (
Fig. 27C
): Oviscapt (eighth sternite) brown, strongly sclerotized, and cylindrical; perineal sclerite somewhat small.
